<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Kinged" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Kinged,</orth> 1) made a king: <cit><quote>then am I k. again,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.36" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 36</bibl></cit>. 2) furnished with a king: <cit><quote>she is so idly k.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 26</bibl></cit>. In <bibl n="shak. jn 2.371" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 371</bibl> most M. Edd. <emph>k. of our fears;</emph> O. Edd. <emph>kings of our feare.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>